    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-root",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Skill: TypeDefinitionIntegrity",
      "position": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "width": 820,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Skill: TypeDefinitionIntegrity\n\n**Category:** Validation / Type Integrity\n\n**Intent:** Validate Type Definition graphs against the current v1 contract, report missing identity or authority surfaces, and only propose bounded metadata repairs.\n\nThis graph is the contract."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-scope",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Scope",
      "position": {
        "x": -980,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Scope\n\nThis skill:\n- validates that a type definition declares `name`, `key`, `classRef`, and `meaning`\n- validates that the referenced class path is present and legible\n- validates that legend-facing identity is declared in data instead of being guessed from the view\n- reports drift in category or status metadata\n\nThis skill does NOT:\n- invent a new type key without review\n- choose a different class authority silently\n- rewrite a view to own semantic identity"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-reads",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Reads",
      "position": {
        "x": -160,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Reads\n\n- type definition node data\n- legend-facing labels and keys\n- class references\n- any `typeSourceNodeId` relationships from views or host consumers"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-writes",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Writes",
      "position": {
        "x": 420,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Writes\n\n- bounded metadata repairs to the type definition node\n- diagnostic notes about missing required fields\n- suggested alignment between type declarations and consuming views"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-failure",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Failure Modes",
      "position": {
        "x": 1000,
        "y": 380
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Failure Modes\n\n- ambiguous class authority\n- missing stable `key`\n- type name present only in a view\n- host consumers depending on inferred rather than declared type\n\nWhen the meaning is unclear, the skill should report ambiguity instead of inventing semantic identity."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-skill-notes",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Notes For AI",
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": 740
      },
      "width": 760,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Notes For AI\n\nPrefer same-name fields when type semantics overlap with other nodesets. A `ui-view` may display the type, but the declared `type-definition` node remains the source of truth."
      }
    }
  ],
